What is a Database?
Define it and explain it in detail.
  It's a set of data that is structured in such a way that it can be accessed in multiple different ways.
  Many different operations can be done with them and they're used in many day to day applications. Examples are Google.
  
Mention at least 5 different Types of Databases.
  Big data databases
  Relational databases
  Operational databases
  Distributed databases
  Object Oriented databases
  
What Does Relational means in the Database world?
  It's a set of data that is organized in tables. In relational databases, the data can be accessed and reassembled in a lot of ways but
  you don't have to reorganize the data-tables. The data is sorted into pre-determined catagories that are then easily accessed.
